PN,41704
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F417A1778249473
OL,3,CZoo staff say public have reported
OL,4,C'several sightings' of missing
OL,5,Ccapybara Samba
OL,7,FWill Walker, Head of Animals and
OL,8,FPlants at Marwell Wildlife said: "Our
OL,9,Flast confirmed sighting of Samba,
OL,10,Fsupported by photographic evidence,
OL,11,Fwas in the Colden Common area on
OL,12,FSunday 22nd March 2026.
OL,14,F"Since then, we've received many
OL,15,Fpossible sightings, but without photos
OL,16,For video, it has been difficult to
OL,17,Fconfirm whether these reports are
OL,18,FSamba or muntjac deer which can look
OL,19,Fvery similar.
OL,26,@pD@bOU
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G4/7
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
