PN,41705
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F417A1778249473
OL,3,CZoo staff say public have reported
OL,4,C'several sightings' of missing
OL,5,Ccapybara Samba
OL,7,F"On Thursday 23rd April, we received
OL,8,Fnew information from a river bailiff
OL,9,Fwho reported seeing an animal feeding
OL,10,Fon vegetation along the riverbank.
OL,12,F"Due to the dense foliage, the animal
OL,13,Fitself was not visible, but the bite
OL,14,Fmarks and the height of the grazed
OL,15,Fplants were consistent with capybara
OL,16,Ffeeding.
OL,18,F"The bailiff noted that this was not
OL,19,Fbehaviour they had observed from other
OL,20,Fspecies they've studied, so we are
OL,21,Fhopeful this may have been Samba.
OL,26,@oD@AOU
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G5/7
